    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the submission on the basis of the 8.3 % mean NIH agreement demonstrated in the steady-state validation study, treating this as sufficient evidence of predictive adequacy for the VAD pulsatile COU. The team noted the pulsatile data gap but considered the steady-state comparator a conservative surrogate. This acceptance is erroneous: the steady-state comparator is methodologically inappropriate for the declared COU2 pulsatile operating envelope (W-AR-05, D3 undercutting). Seven of thirteen credibility factors achieved levels below required levels; six factors were not assessed. The decision outcome is recorded as Accepted to expose the adversarial weakness embedded in this synthetic package.",
